CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 29, 1963, pg. 19, reads: "1963 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama Exhibitors who were not shown on last week's picture page are shown here... 18. Free Hot Dogs Co-op Booth: Charles Murphy, representative, Michael Jackson, Alton Peterson and Gerald Owens serving Shelly Wieners of Buffalo, N.Y., on Ward's Tip Top Buns with Heinz's mustard. All Home-A-Rama Photos (Including last week's) by Charles (Teenie) Harris."
TitMainTitle: Double exposure: Men and boys, possibly including Charles Murphy, Michael Jackson, Alton Peterson, Gerald Owens, and young man wearing Fifth Avenue Archers sweatshirt standing behind Tip Top Bakers table handing hot dog to man, at 1963 Pittsburgh Courier - WAMO, Home-A-Rama fair, Syria Mosque
